        <h3>🥈 Best Alternative: Branch Ergonomic Chair</h3>
        <p>If you can stretch your budget to ~$329, the <a class="internal-link" href="/reviews/branch-ergonomic-chair-review/">Branch Ergonomic Chair</a> is the obvious upgrade. It offers 4D armrests, adjustable seat depth, and a 5-year warranty — all things the Hbada lacks. Read our full <a class="internal-link" href="/reviews/branch-ergonomic-chair-review/">Branch Ergonomic Chair review</a> for details.</p>

        <h3>👑 Premium Alternative: Herman Miller Aeron</h3>
        <p>If budget is no object and you want the gold standard, the <a class="internal-link" href="/reviews/herman-miller-aeron-review/">Herman Miller Aeron</a> is the chair most reviewers benchmark against. It's 10x the price of the Hbada but offers a 12-year warranty, full mesh suspension, and unmatched durability. See our <a class="internal-link" href="/reviews/herman-miller-aeron-review/">Aeron review</a> for whether it's worth it.</p>

        <h3>💰 Budget Alternative: Gabrylly Ergonomic Chair</h3>
        <p>If the Hbada is sold out or you want a higher weight capacity (280 lbs), the Gabrylly at $170 is the next-best budget pick. Full mesh lumbar and flip-up armrests make it ideal for tight spaces. Compare it head-to-head in our <a class="internal-link" href="/compare/">compare</a> tool, or browse other options on our <a class="internal-link" href="/alternatives/">alternatives</a> page.</p>
